U.S. Job Openings Decreased in January; Hirings Also Fell

-- B y   B o b   W i l l i s
-- 
2011-03-11T15:07:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/u-s-job-openings-decreased-in-january-hirings-also-fell.html
Job openings in the U.S. decreased
in January, a sign companies were cautious about hiring as the
new year began.  The number of positions waiting to be filled fell to 2.76
million in January from from a revised 2.92 million in the
previous month, the Labor Department said in a report posted on
its website today.  The number of people hired fell to 3.71 million from 3.91
million, while the number of workers fired decreased to 1.52
million from 1.68 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bob Willis in Washington at 
